"```sql\nSELECT \n    SUM(b1.amount) / SUM(b2.amount) AS ratio\nFROM \n    budget b1\nJOIN \n    event e1 ON b1.link_to_event = e1.event_id\nJOIN \n    budget b2 ON b2.category = 'Advertisement' AND b2.link_to_event = e2.event_id\nJOIN \n    event e2 ON b2.link_to_event = e2.event_id\nWHERE \n    b1.category = 'Advertisement' AND e1.event_name = 'Yearly Kickoff' \n    AND e2.event_name = 'October Meeting';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the ratio of the total budget amount for the \"Advertisement\" category between the \"Yearly Kickoff\" and \"October Meeting\" events. It uses the `budget` and `event` tables, joining them on the `link_to_event` and `event_id` columns to filter and sum the amounts for the specified events."